gomodel:SYNGO_1628  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: CRMP2 was shown to interact with CaV2.2. Overexpression of CRMP2 increases in surface levels of CaV2.2 and is associated with an increase in CaV2.2-mediated Ca2+ currents.. Experimental description: Methods \"Isolation and Culture of Hippocampal Neurons-Rat hippocampal neuron cultures were prepared from hippocampi dissected from PN1 rats as described (30).\"\n\nSupplementary Methods \"Cloning CRMPs and CaVx channel fragments into pGEX-Glu vectors. Using Vector NTI (v. 11; Invitrogen) software, primers were designed to amplify regions corresponding to intracellular loops of rat CaV2.2 cDNA from P3 rat brain cDNA.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5615-1014" ;
        dc:date           "2018-05-29" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_1628" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

